originalText.text: It's your standard Deli. You can find the usual collection. It was reasonably organized. They also have good food choice to grab and go. All in all you can count on it as your usual neighborhood no frills bodega with some interesting smoking device collections :) if you're around it gets the job done.

originalText.text:
Went in for a small milk this morning, I had eight dollars in my hand, the cashier saw it and charged me eight dollars exactly.
Most places will charge around $2.00/2.50 for a quart of milk.
I assume the cashier thought i was a tourist and he could rip me off.
It has backfired as i have moved into the building next door and would have shopped here a lot, but I will never enter the place again.
Do yourself a favor and walk 30 seconds more to the deli on 100th Street.

originalText.text: Had a great Ruben half way through my hike in Central Park. Very good and filling. Great "local" feel in such a big city. Didn't see a lot of seating, so I went to the park to eat. Not a bad compromise
